        <name type="place" key="Cascade County, Mont.">Cascade County</name>, the 
        <name type="place" key="Half-Breed (Pine Island) Rapids">Pine Island Rapid</name>of 
        <hi rend="italic">Atlas</hi>map 62. In this vicinity 
        <name type="person" key="Lewis, Meriwether">Lewis</name>made his camp for the day. Coues
        (HLC), 2:416; MRC map 79.</note>
            <note xml:id="n17071604" n="4">The mountains are composed of the 
        <name type="place" key="Adel Mountains">Adel Mountains</name>volcanics of Paleocene age.
        Near the river the rocks are principally pyroclastic in origin. There is no granite here.
        The rocks are usually described as pale, red, reddish-purple, brown, and gray in
